<br>
I know that was more a rhetorical question than a serious one, but I'll attempt to answer it anyways. What I believe you're complaining about with that post is the tendency of folks to misunderstand the mage class, what it can do for a guild and so on.<br>
<br>
The way we're organized seeks to prevent that sort of issue. Officers in the guild are &quot;class officers.&quot; We are looking for a talented mage to step up and lead his class. As leader of the class he is expected to speak up on behalf of Mage interests when we raid and when we select venues for raiding. <br>
<br>
I like to believe that this sort of structure, where a person with KNOWLEDGE of mages is given responsibility for their happiness and productivity in the guild, will broaden the guild's use of mages and strengthen us as a whole.<br>
<br>
